<br>
Some of you were on last Sunday to see me go into a frantic cursing spree of frustration (appologies for my languge) - this is what happened and what I've been told about it by the Server's GM...<br>
<br>
I was standing in the spires in GD and had logged Hope on to hand me back my FBSS I had loaned to her.  When I tried to hand it to Dresdin - it vanished into thin air.<br>
<br>
After talking with the GM - what actually happened is, Hope handed the FBSS to the &quot;Mystic Voice&quot; that announces the spires activation times...  <br>
<br>
Since this NPC is not visable nor targetable - you will NOT get the standard NPC trading window you would normally get to allow you to cancel giving the item to them...  <br>
<br>
ERGO if you accidently drop your item onto this invisable entity - you get NO CHANCE TO UNDO and the item is LOST...<br>
<br>
Worse yet, the GM has said that since the log will show it as giving the item to an NPC, until Verant changes their policy or makes an exception for this bug..... <br>
<br>
- THEY CAN NOT REIMBURSE ITEMS GIVEN TO A NPC -<br>
<br>
(given - our server's GM is a nice guy and after about 30 or 45 minutes of me bitchin and moaning, he did reimburse my lost FBSS but said he would not reimburse anything else)<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
So what this all boils down to is:<br>
<br>
- DO NOT DO TRADES INSIDE THE SPIRES -<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------<br>
